<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>ART.evo</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            background-color: #f5f5dc; /* Beige */
            color: #5c4033; /* Brown */
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }
        header {
            background-color: #8f9779; /* Green */
            color: white;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        nav {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-around;
            background-color: #d2b48c; /* Light Brown */
            padding: 10px;
        }
        nav a {
            color: #5c4033;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .container {
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .button {
            background-color: #8f9779;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 15px 30px;
            margin: 10px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 16px;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        .button:hover {
            background-color: #6b8e23; /* Darker Green */
        }
        .quiz {
            text-align: left;
            margin: 20px auto;
            max-width: 600px;
            background-color: #ffffff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        .quiz h3 {
            color: #5c4033;
        }
        .quiz label {
            display: block;
            margin: 10px 0;
            color: #5c4033;
        }
        .thank-you {
            padding: 50px;
            text-align: center;
            color: #5c4033;
            background-color: #f5f5dc;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Welcome to ART.evo</h1>
        <p>Explore the history of art or learn how to create your own masterpiece!</p>
    </header>
    <nav>
        <a href="#history">Art History</a>
        <a href="#techniques">Learn Techniques</a>
        <a href="#quiz">Take a Quiz</a>
        <a href="#thank-you">Thank You</a>
    </nav>
    <div class="container">
        <h2>What would you like to do?</h2>
        <button class="button" onclick="location.href='#history'">Learn About Art History</button>
        <button class="button" onclick="location.href='#techniques'">Learn Art Techniques</button>
    </div>
    <div id="quiz" class="container">
        <h2>Art Quiz</h2>
        <div class="quiz">
            <h3>1. Who painted the Mona Lisa?</h3>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="a"> A. Vincent van Gogh</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="b"> B. Pablo Picasso</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="c"> C. Leonardo da Vinci</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="d"> D. Claude Monet</label>
        </div>
        <div class="quiz">
            <h3>2. What is the primary medium used in watercolor painting?</h3>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="a"> A. Oil</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="b"> B. Pigment and water</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="c"> C. Acrylic</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="d"> D. Pastels</label>
        </div>
        <div class="quiz">
            <h3>3. Which of these is a famous art movement?</h3>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="a"> A. Renaissance</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="b"> B. Baroque</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="c"> C. Impressionism</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="d"> D. All of the above</label>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div id="thank-you" class="thank-you">
        <h2>Thank You for joining our game, until next time!</h2>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
